  "notes": "Standard Gujarati (Gujarat, India). Distinct Gujarati script derived from Devanagari. ⟨ળ⟩ = [ɭ] retroflex lateral is a phoneme (unlike most IA). Four-way laryngeal contrast retained. Short /ə/ deleted in word-final position (schwa deletion).",
